Emerging market corporate bonds – defaulting on preconceptions
Emerging market corporate bonds have become a very large asset class. As of January 2017, the value of bonds issued by emerging market companies in hard currency – typically US dollars – as opposed to local currency, totalled US$1.85 trillion.
